types of problems and

00:00:57.016 --> 00:00:59.087
projects mobile programmers work on.

00:00:59.087 --> 00:01:03.129
Mobile developers work on projects
such as building apps that

00:01:03.129 --> 00:01:06.590
are responsive on different devices.

00:01:06.590 --> 00:01:09.170
Creating apps with
a clean user interface so

00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:12.030
that it's intuitive and easy to use.

00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:15.780
Syncing apps to servers so
that it can present data to a user.

00:01:17.160 --> 00:01:22.070
Taking apps from a functional state to a
production ready state through handling

00:01:22.070 --> 00:01:27.560
cases, accessibility features,
localization widgets, and libraries.

00:01:27.560 --> 00:01:32.340
Building high performance apps by taking
advantage of mobile device hardware

00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:33.860
such as cameras and microphones.

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:38.720
The Medium app is a great example
of a well designed mobile app.

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:41.030
It's responsive to
different screen sizes and

00:01:41.030 --> 00:01:42.470
there's a clean user interface.

00:01:43.690 --> 00:01:47.980
It also syncs with different servers to
get data from websites like Twitter and

00:01:47.980 --> 00:01:49.760
other new services.

00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:54.180
It also takes advantage of mobile
device hardware such as the camera, so

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:57.160
that users can take pictures and
post them to their Medium blog.

